    "It was officially announced by Google on February 6, 2023, with the aim of allowing users to interact with search queries in a conversational manner.",
    "Bard is built upon the Gemini large language model, which succeeded earlier models like PaLM 2 and LaMDA.",
    "These models, including Gemini, are grounded in Google's Transformer architecture, a neural network framework released in 2017 [19]. 4.2.1.",
    "Training Methodology and Algorithms Bard's training methodology involves the use of large language models, particularly the Gemini model, to understand and generate human-like responses in conversations.",
    "The underlying architecture, based on Transformers, enables Bard to capture contextual dependencies and semantic understanding in natural language."
